HEADWORD: Soft-hearted
<hw>Soft"-heart`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having softness
or tenderness of heart; susceptible of pity or other kindly affection;
gentle; meek.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Soft"-heart`ed*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

